  "2026-07-14T21:49:50.034Z",maintainer-agent,"GitHub toggle attempt 2026-07-14: PATCH /repos with security_and_analysis.secret_scanning_non_provider_patterns/.secret_scanning_validity_checks = enabled returns 200 but the values stay 'disabled' (verified via GET after retry with JSON body and form syntax) — silently ignored for this user-namespace public repo; these two appear UI-gated. Maintainer UI path: Settings → Advanced Security → Secret Protection → enable 'Non-provider patterns' and 'Validity checks' (both FREE on public repos). Already-enabled free surface verified live: secret_scanning, secret_scanning_push_protection, dependabot_security_updates, private vulnerability reporting."
  "2026-07-14T21:55:56.383Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation: TruffleHog job added to security.yml — trufflesecurity/trufflehog@27b0417c (v3.95.9), fetch-depth:0, extra_args '--results=verified,unknown --exclude-paths=.trufflehog-exclude-paths.txt'. Local full-history scan with the pinned binary: 0 verified secrets; sole 'unknown' = deliberate test fixture https://[redacted-test-fixture-uri] in tests/unit/health-command.spec.ts (DNS-unverifiable) — excluded via unanchored path regex (anchored ^...$ does NOT match in git mode; trap noted). Post-exclusion scan exit 0 / 0 findings printed."
  "2026-07-14T22:03:22.432Z",maintainer-agent,"Gate self-test (first live catch): the initial push went RED because my own implementation comment quoted the basic-auth fixture URI verbatim — the literal landed in this item's history JSONL and TruffleHog flagged the pm store itself (2 unknown results, exit 183). Remediation: pm history-redact pm-4ris (regex redaction, 1 replacement, hash chain recomputed, verify_ok:true — first production use of history-redact) + excluded this item's two store paths in .trufflehog-exclude-paths.txt because the pre-redaction literal is permanent in git blob history. Rule reinforced: NEVER quote secret-pattern literals into pm text, even to describe a fixture. Full-history rescan with pinned binary: 0 findings."
